      <sec id="article-25114.s10" sec-type="Enhancing Healthcare Team Outcomes ">
        <title>Enhancing Healthcare Team Outcomes </title>
        <p>Like other pathogen and infection control,&#x000a0;<italic toggle="yes">Microsporidia</italic> should be managed and prevented with&#x000a0;improved&#x000a0;hygiene. The improved regulation of water sources, as well as monitoring of excrement in soil and water, are important to lessen waterborne disease transmission. The tight regulation and hygiene improvement procedure in food chain production or industry, including breeding, processing, storing and packaging to control food contamination and pathogen spread, are an crucial.</p>
      </sec>
